We recommended that Management prepare and issue a well-defined set of policies and guidelines governing the implementation of AICS program which must be aligned with the guidelines issued by the Department of Social Welfare and Development (DSWD) governing the grants of AICS.  The policies and guidelines shall contain the following:

Kind of financial assistance (burial, transportation, medical, educational, food, shelter and others);

Limitations on the amounts given per kind of financial assistance;

Criteria in granting the financial assistance and the documentary requirements for each particular case; and

Well defined roles and responsibilities of the officials processing requests.

We recommended that Management:

Enjoin the Local DRRM Office (LDRRMO) to exert more effort in implementing actions and measures pertaining to all aspects of disaster risk reduction and management towards building a disaster-resilient Local Government Unit (LGU) and communities;

Closely monitor the implementation of all program, projects and activities (PPAs) under the LDRRM Fund to facilitate corrective action, if any, and the timely reprogramming and reallocation of the fund for its optimum utilization;

Direct the LDRRMO to prepare the annual LDRRMF Investment Plan detailing all the PPAs to be funded in accordance with COA Circular 2012-002 to ensure proper evaluation of the same;


Advise the Municipal Budget Officer see to it that all charges in the LDRRM Fund are related to four (4) thematic areas of DRRM as prescribed in NDRRMC, DBM and DILG JMC 2013-1; and


Instruct the MDRRMC to prioritize the utilization of the unexpended balances of LDRRMF for CYs 2015 and 2016 to ensure that these funds are used for the intended purpose within the prescribed period.

We recommended that Management:

Expedite the completion/updating of the 10-year Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan for approval by the National SWM Commission (NSWMC) to serve as guide for the efficient management of solid waste generated within the Municipality’s jurisdiction;


Prioritize SWM programs and projects by providing/allocating enough budget for their full implementation;

Encourage and provide needed assistance to the remaining 15 barangays to establish their own Materials Recovery Facility (MRFs) for the collection, segregation, recycling of biodegrable, recyclable, compostable and reusable wastes;

Provide adequate assistance in restoring the two not functional barangay MRFs;

Involve closely the Barangay Officials in the strict implementation of the existing environmental laws and intensify the information campaign on the “no segregation, no collection policy” among the residents;

Provide the necessary training for SWM personnel to ensure that solid wastes are properly handled and that the risk of hazards to them and to the public are avoided or minimized; and 


Exert continuous effort in preserving and protecting the environment by implementing the environmental laws as mandated under RA No. 9003.

We reiterated our prior year’s recommendation that the LSB comply strictly with the requirements of Section 272 of RA No. 7160 and DECS-DBM-DILG JC Nos. 01 s. 1998, 01-A s. 2000 and 01-B s. 2001, as follows:

Identify the PPAs that reflect an equitable distribution of the mandated priority expenses and refrain from using the SEF outside the scope for which it was established to avoid disallowance in audit;

Maximize the implementation of the identified and prioritized PPAs to ensure efficient utilization of the fund so that its objectives are fully achieved.

We recommended that Management prepare and issue a well-defined set of policies and guidelines governing the implementation of AICS program which must be aligned with the guidelines issued by the DSWD governing the grants of AICS.  The policies and guidelines shall contain the following:
Kind of financial assistance (burial, transportation, medical, educational, food, shelter and others);
Limitations on the amounts given per kind of financial assistance;
Criteria in granting the financial assistance and the documentary requirements for each particular case; and
Well defined roles and responsibilities of the officials processing requests.

